content:
✅ Approved the contribution.
Comment: Interesting concept, challenging as well! I'm the last person to approve, so congrats, you know have your own clash :)

✅ Approved the contribution.
Comment: It's an interesting and challenging puzzle for Clash of Clans.

Agreed with StepBack. 

I really liked playing it out, but it did take me longer than 5 minutes (under normal non-reverse conditions, but as StepBack mentioned, looking at the test cases, I don't think that would have sped anything up or slowed anything down)

It's a creative clash that surprisingly works really well for Reverse.
I solved in under 15 minutes, and am sure it def could be solved in under 5.

If the community agrees that it can be solved in under 5 minutes, I'd really like to see this as a clash :)
Nice clash, it took me longer than 5 minutes under Reverse conditions, but I don't think I would've been much faster with the statement. It seems a bit hard for a clash, but it is fun to solve.

✅ Approved the contribution.
Comment: Good clash puzzle.

Goal
* Please change "tree given" to "tree. Given".

Input
* Please add "<<Line 1>>:" before "[[n]]".

* Please change "[[n]] lines" to "<<Next [[n]] lines>>".

* Please change "{{parent => child1,...,childN}}" to "[[parent]] {{=>}} [[child1]]{{,}}...{{,}}[[childN]]".

* Please add "<<Next line>>:" before "[[p]]".

Stub generator
* Please add a write statement, e.g. "write answer".

Cases
* Test 4 and Validator 4 are the same. Please change them so that they are similar but different.

Thanks.

I was able to solve in <5min because the idea is almost the same as my own clash :) https://www.codingame.com/contribute/view/993450e019f525af371899a14385c22d73a67

So if people said that one can be solved in <5min then so can this one (I think?)
I think you mean Clash of Code instead of Clash of Clans.
